    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. can you finish option 2? also, the candidate was actually really impressive, especially with their cloud architecture experience. i want the email to acknowledge that they were a strong contender so it doesn't feel like a generic template. can you adjust option 2 to reflect that they were a standout?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is the completed Option 2, tailored to acknowledge their impressive skills, especially in cloud architecture.\n\n**Option 2 (Revised): Warm and Specific**\n\nSubject: Following Up on the Senior Software Engineer Role at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you again for investing your time and energy into the interview process for the Senior Software Engineer role. We were genuinely impressed with your technical depth, and your expertise in cloud architecture, in particular, truly stood out to the entire team. It was a tough decision, as you were certainly a standout contender. We have decided to move forward with another candidate whose specific experience aligned slightly more closely with the immediate, niche requirements of this particular team at this moment.\n\nPlease know this was a difficult choice, and we sincerely value the time you spent with us. We hope you'll keep [Company Name] in mind for future opportunities that might be a better fit for your exceptional talents.\n\nWe wish you the absolute best in finding a role where you can thrive.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n\n***\n\n*A quick note on delivery: When you send this, try to make sure the tone in your actual email matches the warmth of the words. Don",
      "source": "target",
